<h2>1. Install Prowl</h2>
<p>
  Find Prowl in the <a href="https://apps.shopify.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shopify App Store</a> and click "Add app". You'll be redirected to your Shopify admin to approve the installation.
</p>
<p>
  Prowl only requests <strong>read-only</strong> access to your product catalog — it never modifies your store data.
</p>

<h2>2. Activate your plan</h2>
<p>
  After installing, you'll be prompted to start your 14-day free trial ($10/month after trial). All features are fully available during the trial — no limitations.
</p>

<h2>3. Add product pages</h2>
<p>
  From the dashboard, click "Add product page" and select up to 3 products from your catalog. We recommend choosing your highest-traffic or highest-revenue products for monitoring.
</p>

<h2>4. Run your first scan</h2>
<p>
  Click "Scan now" on any product page to trigger an immediate scan. The scan takes about 45–60 seconds. Once complete, you'll see the page status update to Healthy, Warning, or Critical.
</p>
<p>
  After your first manual scan, Prowl will automatically scan all your monitored pages daily at 6:00 AM UTC.
</p>

<h2>5. Configure alerts</h2>
<p>
  Go to <strong>Settings</strong> to customize where alert emails are sent. By default, alerts go to your Shopify store owner email. You can set a different email address and toggle email or admin notifications on or off.
</p>

<h2>What happens next?</h2>
<p>
  Prowl monitors your pages every day. When an issue is detected, you'll see it on your dashboard and (for high-severity issues) receive an email alert with a screenshot, an explanation, and a suggested fix. Issues automatically resolve when Prowl confirms they've been fixed.
</p>
